KW  - Imported
KW  - In-house technologies
KW  - India
AB  - This paper examines whether enterprises' decisions to import technology are influenced by their in-house technological capabilities and whether the imports subsequently lead to an increase in the R&D intensities. It is argued that in a competitive market situation these decisions could be linked in a sequential relationship, but protectionist regulatory policies may make such a relationship quite unlikely. Empirical tests with data of Indian enterprises in the electrical and electronic industries, circa 1990, found results consistent with the predictions for the protected regulatory situation.
ER  - 
